-- Rhineland-Palatinate Premier to Step Down, Tagesspiegel Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-05-09T07:01:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/rhineland-palatinate-premier-to-step-down-tagesspiegel-reports.html
Kurt Beck , the premier of Germany’s
Rhineland-Palatinate regional state, plans to step down this
month,  Tagesspiegel  reported, without saying where it obtained
the information.  Beck, a member of the Social Democratic Party, is likely to
propose Roger Lewentz, the state’s interior minister, as his
successor, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
